Some police forces in cities of the U.S. were in difficulty in the
late 1980s-early 1990s with charges of racism, brutality and false
arrest.

The Los Angeles Police Department was prominent in these charges.
Police chiefs were blamed.

One district attorney refused to prosecute suspects who claimed police
brutality.</SUM>
